<DOC><DOCNO> AP880309-0045 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-09-88 0212EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-JapanMarkets     03-09 0147</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Japan Markets,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Dollar Closes Higher Against Yen; Stocks Sharply Higher</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The dollar rose slightly in Tokyo on Wednesday,while stock prices gained substantially following an overnightadvance on Wall Street.   The dollar closed at 128.08 yen, up 0.28 yen from Tuesday'sclose. It opened at 127.80 yen and ranged between 127.73 yen and128.27 yen.   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the 225-share Nikkei Stock Average,which lost 150.85 points Tuesday, gained back 139.66 points, or0.55 percent, closing at 25,605.39. Trading was relatively heavy at1.3 billion shares.   Michio Katsumata of Nomura Securities, Japan's largest brokeragehouse, said Tokyo stock prices were supported by Tuesday's rally onthe New York Stock Exchange and by stabilization of the foreignexchange market.   Investors also appeared to be buying shares deemed to be atbargain prices after the Tokyo market's decline on Tuesday, dealerssaid.</TEXT></DOC>